<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 25 at 2:14PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of
northeastern Alleghany, central Rockbridge, south central Bath and
north central Botetourt Counties in west central Virginia and the
City of Lexington through 245 PM EDT...
At 214 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Iron Gate, or over Clifton Forge, moving east at 50 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Lexington...
Clifton Forge...
Collierstown...
Rockbridge Baths...
Iron Gate...
Cornwall...
and Low Moor.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
